Comment in
    Eur Heart J. 2005 Mar;26(5):431-2.

AIMS: To investigate the results of endovascular stent-graft placement for the 
treatment of patients with type B aortic dissection (B-AD).
METHODS AND RESULTS: A total of 38 patients (62+/-10 years, 32 male) with acute 
(n=10) and chronic (n=28) type B-AD were treated with endovascular stent-grafts. 
The implantation procedure was successful in all patients. Peri-procedural 
